{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-js","path":"/scope-&-closures-in-javascript/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/scope-&-closures-in-javascript/"},"id":"2a9a90b1-b26c-5ff6-88b6-417958c0ccef","html":"<h1 id=\"scope\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#scope\" aria-label=\"scope permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Scope</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>javascript divides programs into scopes, which can be functions or blocks</li>\n<li>scopes help identify which variable to use when a variable is referenced</li>\n<li>scopes can be nested (scope chaining)</li>\n<li>programs can follow two scoping mechanisms in general -\n<ul>\n<li>lexical scope</li>\n<li>dynamic scope</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>lexical scopes are static i.e. scopes are made during a pre-processing step. javascript only has lexical scope\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">question</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> question<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">otherClass</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"suzy\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"why?\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">otherClass</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// kyle why</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>in dynamic scope, the referenced variable can change depending on the execution context. so, dynamic scopes are made at runtime. for the above example, with dynamic scope, output would have been suzy why</li>\n<li>if javascript doesn’t find something in current scope, it goes one scope up i.e. to its parent scope</li>\n<li>so, scopes can be nested (scope chaining)\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> topic <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"js\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">func</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>topic<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">func</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// js</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"automatically-global\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#automatically-global\" aria-label=\"automatically global permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Automatically Global</h1>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">func</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  topic <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"js\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">func</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>topic<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// js</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>let / var / const was never used with topic. javascript wanted to provide a fallback mechanism, so it creates topic in the global scope</li>\n<li>to prevent this behavior, we can use strict mode</li>\n<li>to enable strict mode, we can use <code class=\"language-text\">\"use strict\"</code> at the top of the js file</li>\n<li>in this case, the code given above fails with <code class=\"language-text\">ReferenceError: topic is not defined</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"functions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#functions\" aria-label=\"functions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Functions</h1>\n<p>functions can be of following types -</p>\n<ul>\n<li>function declaration</li>\n<li>function expression\n<ul>\n<li>named function expression</li>\n<li>anonymous function expression</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>arrow function</li>\n</ul>\n<p>syntax of each -</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">declaration</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">namedExpression</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">named</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">anonymousExpression</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">arrow</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>in case of named function expression -</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the variable to which the function is assigned, is in the same scope</li>\n<li>another readonly variable is created, with the name of the function, inside the function’s scope</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// namedExpression can be used</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">namedExpression</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">named</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// named can be used</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// namedExpression can be used too, since it is in parent scope</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>best practices -</p>\n<ul>\n<li>using function declarations (at the bottom of the file) with executable code at the top. this is possible because of hoisting which is discussed later</li>\n<li>if you have to use function expression, prefer named one because of reasons like -\n<ul>\n<li>reliable readonly variable to use inside the function</li>\n<li>helps in stack trace</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"avoiding-collisions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#avoiding-collisions\" aria-label=\"avoiding collisions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Avoiding Collisions</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>collisions i.e. variables getting redefined can be avoided by using iife or block scopes</li>\n<li>they also prevent from cluttering code with variables that are needed for only one-off tasks</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"iife\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#iife\" aria-label=\"iife permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IIFE</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>immediately invoked function expressions</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">iife</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"suzy\"</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// suzy</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// kyle</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"block\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#block\" aria-label=\"block permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Block</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>blocks can exist by themselves, or parts of if / loops</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">var</code> inside the block scope won’t work since var has function scope</li>\n<li>let and const have block scope</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"suzy\"</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// suzy</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// kyle</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"using-var-vs-let\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#using-var-vs-let\" aria-label=\"using var vs let permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Using Var vs Let</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>var has function scope\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i<span class=\"token operator\">++</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 3</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>let has block scope\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i<span class=\"token operator\">++</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// ReferenceError: i is not defined</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>once var is defined somewhere in the function, it becomes accessible everywhere in that function (or main)</li>\n<li>using var specifies intent i.e. it can be used anywhere in the function</li>\n<li>this makes code more readable compared to let for such cases\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">getTeacher</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// let would work too, var better semantically</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">try</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">retrieveTeacher</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">catch</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>error<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> teacher\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>also, declaring var multiple times doesn’t fail\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// ...</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"suzy\"</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// suzy</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nbut, declaring let multiple times does fail\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// ...</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"suzy\"</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Identifier 'teacher' has already been declared.</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>when we define var in global scope, var gets attached to window object</li>\n<li>this doesn’t happen with let / const</li>\n<li>this behavior of var can be prevented using ‘use strict’</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"hoisting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hoisting\" aria-label=\"hoisting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hoisting</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>javascript moves function, variable declarations, etc. to the top of the scope</li>\n<li>this way, we can call functions and use variables before they are defined\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"how are you\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">question</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>question<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>but only functions declarations are hoisted, not function expressions, because in function expressions, there is an assignment and assignments happen during runtime (hoisting happens before runtime)\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"how are you\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// TypeError: ask is not a function</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">ask</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">question</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>question<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li><strong>all three, var, let and const are hoisted.</strong></li>\n<li>var can be used, it will hold undefined\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\">console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// undefined</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> name <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>let and const are in the tdz (temporal dead zone) state. i.e. cannot be used, until declared in the scope\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\">console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// ReferenceError: teacher is not defined</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>a tricky example for variable hoisting -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"suzy\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">otherTeacher</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">otherTeacher</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// undefined</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nthis happened because the variable teacher was found when it looked inside its own scope, thanks to hoisting</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"closure\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#closure\" aria-label=\"closure permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Closure</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>remembers the variables in a lexical scope even when it is not called from the lexical scope</li>\n<li>the parent scope variables are not garbage collected in the meantime</li>\n<li>examples (based on time) -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">question</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">setTimeout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">answer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>question<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// good, what about you</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// even after sometime, inner scope knows variable in outer scope</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  question <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"good, what about you\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"how are you\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>can reference count even before it was defined, since eventually it is defined\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">setTimeout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>count<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">5000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> count <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>example (based on location) -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">question</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">logQuestion</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>question<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> myQuestion <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"how are you\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">myQuestion</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 'how are you'</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>functions close over a variable, not a value. so, if the variable changes, value changes too\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> teacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kyle\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">question</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>teacher<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> question<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\nteacher <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"suzy\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">ask</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"why\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// suzy why</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"loops-and-scopes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#loops-and-scopes\" aria-label=\"loops and scopes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Loops and Scopes</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>same i is used for the entire block scope of for loop\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i<span class=\"token operator\">++</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">setTimeout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">timer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 3 3 3</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>var isn’t block scoped, its function scoped</li>\n<li>but how to log 1, 2, 3?…use let which is block scoped!\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i<span class=\"token operator\">++</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> j <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> i\n  <span class=\"token function\">setTimeout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">timer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>j<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 1 2 3</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>for each iteration, refers to a different j</li>\n<li>since es6, if we use directly let inside for loops and its variations like <code class=\"language-text\">for (let a of b)</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">for (let a in b)</code>, etc., it automatically is scoped to the block of the loop!\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i<span class=\"token operator\">++</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">setTimeout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">timer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 1 2 3</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Scope & Closures in Javascript"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"2a9a90b1-b26c-5ff6-88b6-417958c0ccef"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1037383464","1617985380"]}